   <string>
The warded creature or object becomes difficult to detect by
divination spells such as clairaudience/clairvoyance, locate
object, and detection spells. Nondetection also prevents location
by such magic items as crystal balls. If a divination is
attempted against the warded creature or item, the caster of the
divination must succeed at a caster level check (1d20 + caster
level) against a DC of 11 + the caster level of the spellcaster
who cast nondetection. If you cast nondetection on yourself or on
an item currently in your possession, the DC is 15 + your caster
level.
If cast on a creature, nondetection wards the creature's
gear as well as the creature itself.
Material Component: Worth 50 gp.
